e. In confronting the continuing challenge of globalization, Malaysians should not neglect the history of ideas — and ideology — as they search for new options.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aMalaysia--Economic policy. 0aMalaysia--Foreign relations. 0aMalaysia--Politics and government. 0aMalaysia--Race relations. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / General.2bisacsh1 aEmbong, Abdul Rahman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKassim, Azizah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMilner, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMilner, Anthony, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNathan, K.S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRahman Embong, Abdul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSiew Yean, Tham, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTing, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYean, Tham Siew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZin, Ragayah Haji Mat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066300608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060668340uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981451792840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789814517928423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814517928.jpg  a978-3-11-060668-3  ISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec